# TypeScript and Prisma Contract Drift Prevention

Avoid contract drift at library boundaries. When integrating Prisma, Base UI, AI SDK, or route handlers, enforce these patterns.

## UI Wrappers (Base UI, Radix, etc.)

Derive event and prop types from the wrapped component instead of hand-writing DOM types:

```ts
// ❌ BAD: guessed DOM Event
const handleSelect = (event: Event) => onSelect?.(event);

// ✅ GOOD: derive from wrapped component
type SelectEvent = Parameters<NonNullable<ComponentProps<typeof DropdownMenuItem>["onSelect"]>>[0];
const handleSelect = (event: SelectEvent) => onSelect?.(event);
```

Place timing props (`openDelay`, `closeDelay`) on the component that actually accepts them; check the upstream API.

## Prisma Singleton

When using multiple init branches (e.g. Accelerate vs standard), export one stable type:

```ts
// ❌ BAD: inferred union causes "This expression is not callable"
const prisma = databaseUrl.startsWith("prisma://")
  ? new PrismaClient().$extends(withAccelerate())
  : new PrismaClient();

// ✅ GOOD: single stable exported type
type PrismaClientSingleton = PrismaClient;
const prisma = (): PrismaClientSingleton =>
  databaseUrl.startsWith("prisma://")
    ? new PrismaClient().$extends(withAccelerate()) as unknown as PrismaClientSingleton
    : new PrismaClient();
```

## AI Tools and Services

Keep app-only context (e.g. `clientId`) in request-scoped factories; do not overload service functions:

```ts
// ✅ GOOD: tools built per request, close over clientId
export const createSearchKnowledgeBaseTool = (clientId: string) =>
  tool({
    inputSchema: z.object({ query: z.string().trim().min(1) }),
    execute: async (input) => agentService.searchKnowledge({ clientId, ...input }),
  });
```

## Route Handlers and Persistence

- Add an explicit serialisation boundary when persisting SDK payloads (e.g. `UIMessage[]`) to Prisma JSON:
  `JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(value)) as Prisma.InputJsonValue`
- Enforce tenant ownership when persisting/reading by `sessionId`: verify `clientId` matches before update/read.
- Add route-level tests when handlers validate JSON or convert third-party payloads.

## Completion Gate

Treat "fix IDE errors" as incomplete until `bun run build` passes. Several contract bugs only surface at compile time.
